ld it be better if MT use evasive to avoid the proc ?  or is defensive still better? what are some of u guys' thoughts ? thx for any opinions <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solinarinnoruuk>Solinar Innoruuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 374<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 12:03:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3035.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mith Marr tanking question</span><hr size=1> I use Evasive to tank just about everything these days.<br>
<br>
Is it better? Thats a matter of opinion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andrath>Andrath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 12:57:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3035.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mith Marr tanking question</span><hr size=1> I use defensive and don't have any problems.  Make sure you have a bard in your group and have 500 MR.  Also make sure one of the wizards is spellshielding you every time the proc lands.  Make sure you land a disease resist slow on him first then land a 75% slow on him after. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=382645"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Boggrak</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Level 65 Warlord</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Order of the Phoenix</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andrath>Andrath</A> at: 3/18/03 4:50:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solinarinnoruuk>Solinar Innoruuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 376<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 2:15:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3035.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mith Marr tanking question</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Make sure you land a 75% slow on him<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I wouldnt plan your raid around landing a MR slow.<br>
<br>
We have had shaman and mages go oom from simply casting malosinia and turgurs and getting resists.<br>
<br>
It is possible to yawn him, but its not normal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karthunk>Karthunk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 2:41:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3035.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mith Marr tanking question</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Make sure you have a bard in your group and have 500 MR.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
Here is the key to the MM fight. <p><a href= http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=110313 target="_blank">Just another dead tank</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 249<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 2:49:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3035.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mith Marr tanking question</span><hr size=1> SK resist debuff is the key to Turgur MM <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
There's a lot of PoP bosses with 3K procs.  The only way to deal with them is resists.  No matter how good is your chain, a back to back 3K proc will most likely mean the end of the tank and it will happen at some point. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaladornus>kaladornus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 10:14:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3035.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mith Marr tanking question</span><hr size=1> Someone want to talk me through pulling the room, since my EQ career unfortunately ended at that point due to an untimely case of marriage? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
We were able to get Frog Boy to come with only two mezzable blue kitties, albeit it was an accident at the time, but if we had been ready and taken out frog man and mezzed the kitties (I saw he had a knockback, but would have been fairly easy to wedge an MA into any of the hall corners) would it just have been a matter of keeping the halls clean while we whittled down the room 2-3 kitties at a time?<br>
<br>
Then bringing beard boy out to a spot free of repops?<br>
<br>
This one encounter sort of haunts me because I only had about 40 or so people show up for it, and we had the halls all clean of named plus that Frog and two mezzables pull made me very hopeful that I could have completed that encounter.<br>
<br>
Just wondering...<br>
<br>
Jak Attack <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solinarinnoruuk>Solinar Innoruuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 380<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 12:08:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3035.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mith Marr tanking question</span><hr size=1> Have a monk FD split everything, and have 2 tank mezzers with dedicated healers ready for adds.  The adds are mezzable iirc, but their MR is cranked and your better off just tank mezzing them sometimes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lumudan>lumudan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 1:31:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3035.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mith Marr tanking question</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>would it be better if MT use evasive to avoid the proc ? or is defensive still better? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Avoid the procs and the encounter is trivial whether you use evasive or defensive.  Tanked him twice and out at least 40+ procs 4 landed and all of those were partials.  Look at the procs, see what resist they are on, deal with them accordingly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showPrevMessage?topicID=3035.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showNextMessage?topicID=3035.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3035.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.emailToFriend?topicID=3035.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.threadControl?topicID=3035.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3035.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3035.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thes